Description: Small complete seal-impression with two small rows of basketry coil impression at the rear and one flat and larger one at the side, showing that this piece was positioned most likely on the lid of a basket. The fine brown Nile clay shows inclusions of mica. At the top one impression of a scarab-like seal that is very eroded and shallow. Visible is a circumferential line and a small illegible cartouche at the side. Same seal as used on EA86691, EA86705, and EA86713.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
